e-tests-only false-GREEN paths on hard tasks)\n23:- HARNESS-EVAL, adversarial verifier, false-GREEN, reference/harness-eval.md, templates/harness-eval-report.md, tests/harness-eval-contract.test.sh, Adversarial Verify, Machine Checks, visible tests only\n29:- rollout_summaries/2026-06-06T13-48-21-JmuG-supergoal_skill_harness_eval_adversarial_verifier_loop_and_s.md (cwd=/Users/danny/Documents/PARA/Resource/supergoal-skill, rollout_path=/Users/danny/.codex/sessions/2026/06/06/rollout-2026-06-06T22-48-21-019e9d31-1b6b-77a1-a5bd-5c0c0a55200e.jsonl, updated_at=2026-06-06T14:30:14+00:00, thread_id=019e9d31-1b6b-77a1-a5bd-5c0c0a55200e, rerun shipped but hidden-edge score did not improve)\n38:- when the user said `make the improvement to th skill` after a false-GREEN rerun -> harden the `supergoal` contract itself, not just the experiment report or case artifact [Task 2]\n43:- `reference/learn.md` is still the load-bearing LEARN prose file. Small readability edits are safe only if they preserve literal anchors and are rechecked with `bash tests/learn-contract.test.sh`, `bash tests/worktree-contract.test.sh`, `bash tests/domain-context-contract.test.sh`, `bash tests/gate-scenarios.test.sh`, and `git diff --check` [Task 1]\n45:- HARNESS-EVAL’s load-bearing surface is split across `SKILL.md`, `reference/harness-eval.md`, `templates/harness-eval-report.md`, and `tests/harness-eval-contract.test.sh`; the route now explicitly includes `Adversarial Verify -> Repair Loop -> Machine Checks` for hard tasks [Task 2]\n52:- symptom: a skill change looks successful because visible tests pass -> cause: HARNESS-EVAL lacked a separate adversarial verifier loop for hidden acceptance edges -> fix: add verifier-authored RED tests, track false-GREEN explicitly, and only trust results after Machine Checks plus blind grading [Task 2][Task 3]\n101:## Task 1: Explain the high-level AIDT LMS domain view and verify `supergoal` in Codex, success\n105:- rollout_summaries/2026-06-04T22-08-14-VBPx-aidt_l